The paper deals with the problem of face alignment, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a novel approach using ensemble learning and decision trees, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves handling different viewpoints and landmark protocols, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
